node.text:
This is Eidfjord 😍 A village situated at the end of the Eid Fjord, an inner branch of the large Hardangerfjorden.

Eidfjord has several tourist sites, like the Sima Power Plant which is built into the mountain itself. 🏔

The power plant, which has the Hardanger Glacier as its water source, is ideally situated for power generation. Here are rivers, cascading waterfalls and plenty of precipitation. The nominal annual production at Sima is 2840 million kWh – or almost the annual consumption of a city the size of Bergen (population: 285,911). 😲🧐

Hydropower is clean and renewable – a literal perpetuum mobile. The sun evaporates the water, which returns as precipitation from which we can generate energy. ⚡️

Since the opening in 1980, the Sima power plant has supplied both Norway and Europe with pure, renewable energy. 

In other words: Perfect to recharge your brand new Volvo XC40 with 100% green electric power 😏😍 #Norway 🇳🇴 #ad #volvocarnorge #volvoxc40 #volvo @volvocarno 

📸: @holm
